/*
 * Uploading new binaries to the ESP32 over Wi-Fi will speed up development.
 * There are examples where the MCU acts as Wi-Fi access point and examples where the
 * firmware of the MCU is updated in over-the-air (OTA) fashion via a Wi-Fi network
 * that is shared between the MCU and the programming laptop.
 * For the Interactive Pole we want to combine these two functionalities. In this way
 * the system does not require a Wi-Fi network to be present and anyone can login to
 * the MCU's Wi-Fi network and access the web server for OTA firmware updates.
 *
 * The [inspiration source code](../../../inspiration/src/main.cpp) uses an external
 Wi-Fi network.

 * https://github.com/bovineck/ESP32-OTA-AP/tree/main
 * https://docs.arduino.cc/libraries/arduinoota/
 * https://github.com/arduino-libraries/Arduino_ESP32_OTA
 */

